longInfo:
Passport required. 
- Passports and/or passport replacing documents issued to
  nationals of French West Indies must be valid on arrival. 
- Nationals of France are allowed to enter with expired (max.
  5 years) National ID Cards issued between 1 January 2004 and
  31 December 2013, provided holder was 18 years of age or
  older on the date of issue. 
Passport Exemptions:
- Holders of a National ID Card issued to nationals of France.
- Holders of emergency or temporary passports.

VISA NOT REQUIRED.

Minors:
- When their names are registered in the passport of (one of)
  their parents or guardians, 
- WARNING! In accordance with European Union (EU) Legislation,
  all minors who are nationals of French West Indies will be
  expected to hold their own passport or National ID Card
  (where applicable) when departing from Bulgaria, Croatia,
  Cyprus, Romania or a Schengen Member State . 
Additional Information:
- Flights between the United Kingdom and the Channel Islands,
  Ireland (Rep.) and Isle of Man are treated as domestic
  flights, therefore are not subject to UK immigration
  control
